{"id": "EUVD-2022-55733", "enisaUuid": "2eb2817a-2a1a-3dc0-9f2b-78341ae4e869", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nmailbox: zynq-ipi: fix error handling while device_register() fails\n\nIf device_register() fails, it has two issues:\n1. The name allocated by dev_set_name() is leaked.\n2. The parent of device is not NULL, device_unregister() is called\n   in zynqmp_ipi_free_mboxes(), it will lead a kernel crash because\n   of removing not added device.\n\nCall put_device() to give up the reference, so the name is freed in\nkobject_cleanup(). Add device registered check in zynqmp_ipi_free_mboxes()\nto avoid null-ptr-deref.", "datePublished": "2025-12-09T18:30:32", "dateUpdated": "2025-12-09T18:30:32", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/b3a5c76f61e2b380e29dfc6705854ca1ee85501d", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/a39b4de0804f9fe0ae911b359ffd4afe7d9d933b", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/4f05d8e2fb3ab702c2633a74571e1b31cb579985", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/f2d63cefc012cafe1b7651bbf3302f8bcd8bea4a", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/3fcf079958c00d83c51e4f250abf2c77fe9cc1b9", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/a6792a0cdef0b1c2d77920246283a72537e60e94", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2022-50672"], "aliases": ["CVE-2022-50672"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.03, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "0155d1cf-3acd-3e7a-a6a3-0e66499e56ef", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.10.163"}, {"id": "32e4db4f-c382-3e3a-a324-5f14847e3932", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "4981b82ba2ff87df6a711fcd7a233c615df5fc79 <b3a5c76f61e2b380e29dfc6705854ca1ee85501d"}, {"id": "3a2542ad-d58c-3489-bd4b-0ac4845e2de1", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "4d62c1e9-daa7-3ae6-9c5d-fe1ab8ce57cd", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "4981b82ba2ff87df6a711fcd7a233c615df5fc79 <a39b4de0804f9fe0ae911b359ffd4afe7d9d933b"}, {"id": "5c915fe3-a4ba-3